Immature stages. Known from images of reared specimens (Figs 139-146). Larva predominantly light brown, faintly shaded with green intersegmentally and laterally on A4-6; coloration generally more uniform above spiracular line, reticulate below; 
the
familiar dorsal herring-bone pattern consisting of a row of Y-shaped markings, the arms of which terminate at the D1 pinacula, which on A1 are partially encircled with anterior cream-colored marking to form a spectacle-like mark. Thoracic segments taper dorsally. Young larvae predominantly greenish gray, with anastomosing pattern visible dorsally; thin white spiracular line beneath a broader reddish-purple supraspiracular line, the upper edge of which runs just above SD1 pinacula.
